<p><a href="#sdfootnote31anc" name="sdfootnote31sym">31</a> “‘Eigentlich müßte jeder verdächtig sein.’ Das Dilemma der Terroristen-Fahdnung: Untergrund in Bürgermaske,” <em>Spiegel, </em>No. 38 (1977): 22-33. Even though the article supposedly deals with the bourgeois mimicry employed by the RAF, it does not show any photos of the underground apartments. This explains Christoph Keller’s reaction when Korpys/Löffler first showed him the photos they had obtained: “They showed me the photos and I thought: these are absolutely unpublished, we definitely have to make these sites public.” <em>build.</em> Interview. (my translation)</p>
